---
// FindingsSection.astro - Displays the findings section with collapsible cards
---
<section id="results" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Key Findings</h2>
    <div class="diagram-placeholder">
      <img src="/figures/results.png" alt="Results comparison chart" />
      <p style="text-align: center; color: #888;">Performance comparison of different approaches on MINDCUBE.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-card">
      <div class="finding-header"><h3 class="finding-title">External scaffolding is surprisingly ineffective</h3></div>
      <div class="finding-content active"><p>Providing models with ground-truth cognitive maps improved performance by only 0.9%, while view interpolation actually decreased performance by 0.6%. Even free-form reasoning prompts, while helpful, provided modest gains of just 1.6%.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-card">
      <div class="finding-header"><h3 class="finding-title">Self-generated spatial representations yield dramatic improvements</h3></div>
      <div class="finding-content active"><p>Teaching models to generate their own cognitive maps and reason over them boosted performance from 38.3% to 61.7%â€”a gain of 23.5 percentage points. Reinforcement learning further increased performance to 76.1% (+37.8%).</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-card">
      <div class="finding-header"><h3 class="finding-title">Why self-generation works: representational dissonance</h3></div>
      <div class="finding-content active"><p>Externally provided maps often conflict with the model's internal spatial processing, leading to confusion. Self-generation ensures alignment between internal representations and reasoning processes, even if the maps are less accurate than ground truth.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="diagram-placeholder">
      <img src="/figures/map-quality.png" alt="Map quality comparison" />
      <p style="text-align: center; color: #888;">Self-generated map quality improves with training and correlates with reasoning performance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-card">
      <div class="finding-header"><h3 class="finding-title">Training pipeline synergy</h3></div>
      <div class="finding-content active"><p>Supervised fine-tuning (SFT) establishes the ability to generate structured spatial representations. Reinforcement learning (RL) refines these capabilities, leading to more accurate maps and more effective reasoning chains.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="finding-card">
      <div class="finding-header"><h3 class="finding-title">Broader impact</h3></div>
      <div class="finding-content active"><p>The principles established by MINDCUBE could inform the development of novel training paradigms for spatial intelligence and internal model construction in AI, with implications for robotics and real-world applications.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .findings-components {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .finding-card {
    background-color: #fff;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .finding-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    transform: translateY(-5px);
  }

  .finding-header {
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: white;
  }

  /* Different background colors for each finding card */
  .finding-card:nth-child(1) .finding-header { background-color: #2a2f6c; }
  .finding-card:nth-child(2) .finding-header { background-color: #4a3f9f; }
  .finding-card:nth-child(3) .finding-header { background-color: #5e56b2; }
  .finding-card:nth-child(4) .finding-header { background-color: #7165d8; }
  .finding-card:nth-child(5) .finding-header { background-color: #9f7cd2; }
  .finding-card:nth-child(6) .finding-header { background-color: #2a2f6c; }

  .finding-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .expand-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    margin-left: 1rem;
  }

  .finding-content {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: none;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .finding-content p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .finding-content.active {
    display: block;
    animation: fadeIn 0.5s ease;
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-10px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  /* Add highlighting for key terms */
  .finding-content strong {
    color: #4a3f9f;
    background-color: rgba(74, 63, 159, 0.1);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    // Set up event listeners for all finding cards
    for (let i = 1; i <= 6; i++) {
      const findingCard = document.getElementById(`finding-card-${i}`);
      const findingContent = document.getElementById(`finding-content-${i}`);
      
      if (findingCard && findingContent) {
        const expandIcon = findingCard.querySelector('.expand-icon') as HTMLElement | null;
        
        // Initialize all cards as expanded
        findingContent.classList.add('active');
        if (expandIcon) {
          expandIcon.textContent = '-';
        }
        
        findingCard.addEventListener('click', (e: Event) => {
          const target = e.target as HTMLElement;
          if (target.closest && target.closest('.finding-content')) return;
          
          findingContent.classList.toggle('active');
          if (expandIcon) {
            if (findingContent.classList.contains('active')) {
              expandIcon.textContent = '-';
            } else {
              expandIcon.textContent = '+';
            }
          }
        });
      }
    }
  });
</script> 